verses.text:
if you are pure and upright,
then even now he will rouse himself on your behalf,
and he will restore your rightful dwelling place.

Don’t you know this?
From ancient times,
from the time when Adam was placed on the earth,

if he hoards it for himself,
and he does not let it go,
but savors it on his palate,

If my footsteps have slipped off the path,
if my heart has pursued things desired by my eyes,
if anything corrupt has stuck to my palms,

In a dream, in a vision in the night,
when people are falling into a deep sleep,
while they slumber on their beds,

if he is gracious to him,
if he says, “Spare him from going down to the pit.
I have found a ransom for him,”
